<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,1562,2093]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,520,1850,1876]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
The species is invasive, found in all regions of 
<collectingCountry box="[1045,1116,1850,1876]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, also widely distributed in the Northeast region (AL, BA, CE, MA, PB, PE, PI, RN, SE) (BFG 2018). It is associated with the Amazon, Caatinga, Cerrado and Atlantic Rainforest domains, and can be found in disturbed environments, roadsides and highway margins (Kill 
<emphasis box="[196,252,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2000).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,1562,2093]" box="[189,1032,1994,2021]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,1994,2020]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Registered with flowers and fruits at October and December.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="9" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,1562,2093]" lastBlockId="10.[136,1452,158,257]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,490,2030,2056]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Taxonomic discussion:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[489,768,2030,2057]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Centrosema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brasilianum">
<emphasis box="[489,768,2030,2057]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="26">Centrosema brasilianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by the vine habit, imparipinnate leaves, raceme axillary inflorescence, mainly by the pedicellated flowers, with 5 violet petals, glabrous, inermous branches. 
<taxonomicName box="[136,270,159,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Centrosema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,270,159,185]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Centrosema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presented two species in the study area, being that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[859,1028,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Centrosema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brasilianum">
<emphasis box="[859,1028,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. brasilianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is trifoliolate with lanceolate leaflets 
<emphasis box="[136,208,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">versus</emphasis>
unifoliolate leaflets, sagitate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brandegee" authorityYear="1905" baseAuthorityName="Humboldt &amp; Bonpland ex Willdenow" baseAuthorityYear="1809" box="[564,714,195,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Centrosema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sagittatum">
<emphasis box="[564,714,195,221]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. sagittatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Next the study area in Cariri paraibano was found four speceis of 
<taxonomicName box="[136,270,231,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Centrosema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,270,231,257]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Centrosema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[325,492,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Centrosema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brasilianum">
<emphasis box="[325,492,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. brasilianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was more comum in all enviroments (
<bibRefCitation author="Queiroz, R. T." box="[923,1079,230,256]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" refId="ref18260" refString="Queiroz, R. T. (2021) Fabaceae do Cariri paraibano. Nova Xavantina, 630 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.46420 / 9786588319604" type="book" year="2021">Queiroz 2021</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
